column1: Investigation of overlap between protein quantitative trait loci (pQTLs) and expression quantitative trait loci (eQTLs)

column2: The markername is in the format of chr:pos:A1_A2, where A1/A2 is by alphabetical sorting
If distance between index SNP and protein encoding gene is larger than 1 MB
A1 is coded allele, meaning that a positive effect size indicates that A1 increases protein level
Overall SCALLOP pQTL P-value as calculated by METAL
Effect size of SCALLOP pQTL given as standard-deviations of protein concentration per A1-allele

Selected according to the criteria for MR instrument variable selection
Whole blood eQTL analysis in the LifeLinesDeep cohort: if the pQTL was testable (1) or not (0). LifeLinesDeep is a SCALLOP-participating cohort with whole blood eQTL measurements available
Whole blood eQTL analysis in the LifeLinesDeep cohort: Estimation of power to detect corresponding eQTL effect
Whole blood eQTL analysis in the LifeLinesDeep cohort: The direction of eQTL effect compared to pQTL effect (0=not significant at FDR<0.05)
Whole blood eQTL analysis in the LifeLinesDeep cohort: The direction of eQTL effect compared to pQTL effect (0=not significant at P<0.05)
Multi-tissue eQTL analysis in GTEx: if the pQTL was testable (1) or not (0). GTEx consist of 48 different tissue types.
Multi-tissue eQTL analysis in GTEx: Tissues with eQTL effects in same direction as the pQTL effect (0=not significant at FDR<0.05)
Multi-tissue eQTL analysis in GTEx: Tissues with eQTL effects in opposite direction as the pQTL effect (0=not significant at FDR<0.05)
Multi-tissue eQTL analysis in GTEx: Tissues with eQTL effects in same direction as the pQTL effect (0=not significant at P<0.05)
Multi-tissue eQTL analysis in GTEx: Tissues with eQTL effects in opposite direction as the pQTL effect (0=not significant at P<0.05)
Whole-blood eQTL analysis in eQTLgen: if the pQTL was testable (1) or not (0). eQTLgen is a large meta-analysis of whole blood and PBMC eQTL
Whole-blood eQTL analysis in eQTLgen: The direction of eQTL effect compared to pQTL effect (0=not significant at FDR<0.05)
Whole-blood eQTL analysis in eQTLgen: The direction of eQTL effect compared to pQTL effect (0=not significant at P<0.05)

Summary of eQTL: Had a signficant association anywhere at P<0.05
